  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into quarters, leaving the skins and root on</p><p>Tip: This stops them drying out and falling apart when roasting!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-6-1649169973647-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-6-1649169973647-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-6-1649169973647-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-6-1649169973647-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-6-1649169973647-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet</strong> <strong>potato</strong> and<strong> onion quarters</strong> to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-30 min or until the onion is tender and the sweet potato is cooked and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1649169980827-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1649169980827-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1649169980827-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1649169980827-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-6-1649169980827-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> with<strong> cling film </strong>and bash them with a<strong> rolling pin </strong>until flattened to roughly 1.5cm thick all over</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-6-1649169990347-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-6-1649169990347-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-6-1649169990347-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-6-1649169990347-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-6-1649169990347-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned, then remove from the heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-6-1649169997344-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-6-1649169997344-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-6-1649169997344-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-6-1649169997344-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-6-1649169997344-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>browned chicken</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil </strong>to avoid mess!)</p><p>Sprinkle your<strong> pine nut & seed mix</strong> all over</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 14-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the juices run clear – this is your <strong>seeded chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1649170005076-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1649170005076-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1649170005076-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1649170005076-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-5-1649170005076-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>chopped dates</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>date dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add to the bowl with the date dressing</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1649170028382-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1649170028382-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1649170028382-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1649170028382-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-5-1649170028382-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables are cooked, carefully cut the roots off the<strong> roasted onion quarters</strong>, then peel off the skins and discard</p><p>Separate the<strong> onion quarters</strong> into petals</p><p>Add the <strong>onion petals </strong>and <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong> to the salad bowl – this is your <strong>sweet potato salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1649170037042-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1649170037042-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1649170037042-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1649170037042-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-5-1649170037042-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> seeded chicken</strong> over the<strong> sweet potato salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle any <strong>remaining date dressing</strong> over the top and sprinkle over any <strong>remaining seeds </strong>from the tray</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
